Ashoka Student, Layasree Vemmata Gopi (@layaaaa_26), from the UG 2024 batch, won the Monaco Ocean Protection Challenge 2025 (@monacoopc) under the Business Concepts category. She was the youngest competitor in this prestigious challenge and won for her compelling idea.

Read about Laya’s journey in her own words:

"I have always been amazed by the ocean, I knew that I had to protect it, hence I started with marine ecology research, which led to me realising the significant negative impact that seafood waste has on our oceans and our planet, which is when I innovated my startup idea, Cool Equity. Cool Equity provides decentralised cold storage to fishermen, helping reduce post-harvest seafood waste using phase change materials. Winning the Monaco Ocean Protection Challenge 2025 under the Business Concepts category has been a great honour where I got to represent our country India on an important global stage for ocean protection as a young woman in STEM which will now help me make my idea a reality starting in India where I can reach MVP and validate the idea with the funding provided. I hope for this to be a step ahead for ocean protection in the Global South."
___

latestPosts.caption:
Are you ready to turn your curiosity into a publish-worthy case study? ✨

The CfE Inquire Fellowship is a 3-month programme designed to help you research and write an in-depth case study on a startup or startup sector, supported by expert faculty mentorship and access to exclusive research resources. 

Why apply? 🎯
- Work 1-on-1 with experienced faculty mentors
- Get reimbursed for approved research expenses
- Connect with entrepreneurs and changemakers in the CfE network
- Receive support in publishing your case with reputable publishers
- Eligible to convert the fellowship into an ENT ISM (based on outcome quality)

By the end of the fellowship on September 30th, selected students will be expected to submit 📌 
- A 5,000+ word narrative case study co-authored with your faculty mentor
- At least 5 pages of annexures with relevant data and figures
- A teaching note to accompany the case

Who’s eligible? 🔑
- Preference will be given to current Ent Minor / Concentration / Interdisciplinary Major students
- Proposals must focus on a startup or a startup sector
- You can apply solo or in pairs (no groups of 3+)
- Preference for proposals with an on-ground fieldwork component

This is your chance to create meaningful research, grow your network, and build something you can proudly publish. 📃

Ready to stand out and make your mark?

 Apply Now – Deadline: 10th June, 2025
 Form Link: https://forms.gle/UFM49FDe6c9fuqz16

Yesterday, the Centre hosted the Academic Reception for the graduating classes of UG '25 and ASP '25. It was a heartwarming morning of celebration, reflection, and pride, recognizing the incredible journeys of our students and the vibrant entrepreneurial spirit they brought to campus.

As part of this special occasion, we were proud to acknowledge the exceptional contributions and accomplishments of several students. Anoushka Singh, Ishan Shanavas, and Shyamali Tewari were awarded for their academic excellence in the ASP Minor in Entrepreneurial Leadership & Strategy. We also celebrated the outstanding commitment of Mridul Malani and Tarini Kochhar with the Service Excellence in Entrepreneurship Award. And finally, the Spirit of Entrepreneurship Award was presented to Prabal Agarwal and Anushka Mittal for exemplifying an enterprising mindset and inspiring leadership throughout the year. As they step into the next phase of their lives, we are confident they will carry this spirit forward, making meaningful contributions to the world beyond Ashoka.

Congratulations once again to the Class of 2025! We are proud to have been part of your journey. 🚀🌻

@anoushkasing.h @ishan.shanavas @shyamalitewari @mridulmalanii @tarinikochhar_ @an.ush.ka.25 @prabal_agarwal12 @ok_rutika @rijulganju
